The paper focuses on analyzing the behavior of different heuristics in tournament selection for a Semantic Genetic Programming system for classification problems. This involves measuring the similarity of individuals in the semantic space, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of genetic operators and classifiers also suggests a connection to neural networks (cs.NE) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper involves testing on a variety of problems, which could fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
